last_episode_to_air.name: The Last Day of Summer
last_episode_to_air.overview: Tilly rounds up her brother and sisters and they set sail on a fishing trip around the beautiful Cornish coast.

name: Matilda and the Ramsay Bunch
overview: Join Matilda as she cooks up a storm and goes on adventures with her family.

episodes.name: The LA Arrival
episodes.overview: The Ramsay family touch down in LA. Matilda cooks up a fantastic celebratory meal full of delicious American flavours - big & bold burgers with Tilly's secret twist, smoky fries, followed by her ice cream Ramsay Whoopies.

episodes.name: The Movies
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay Bunch learn how to make their own action films, and hold their own awards ceremony.

episodes.name: The Monster Party
episodes.overview: Matilda & the Ramsay Bunch cook up super scary food and find out how to levitate. The gang head off to a top special effects studio to get really frightening make-up done - it's so realistic it takes over two hours to put on.

episodes.name: The Beach BBQ
episodes.overview: Matilda & the Ramsay Bunch hit the beach & go totally California crazy! Matilda cooks up a storm by the sea with her herby garlic bread, a delicious clam bake & a real American BBQ classic, sensational s'mores.

episodes.name: The Big Food Fight
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay Bunch set up a food face off - British versus American.

episodes.name: The Bollywood Party
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay Bunch learn some brilliant Bollywood dance moves and cook up some incredible Indian party food.

episodes.name: The US Sportsday
episodes.overview: Matilda & the Ramsay Bunch go sports mad. The world series of beach volleyball takes place in LA. Matilda cooks up a picnic, that's perfect to eat as they watch the exciting comp. LA hot dogs with crunchy coleslaw & pretzels.

episodes.name: The Sleepover
episodes.overview: Matilda & the Ramsay Bunch banish the boys & have a girls only sleepover! Matilda cooks up fantastic food that's perfect for sharing: spiced chicken wings, Californian summer rolls & amazing jellies that glow in the dark.

episodes.name: The Pool Party
episodes.overview: Matilda & the Ramsay Bunch throw the ultimate Californian summer party: wet, wild & so much fun! Matilda is serving up her best ever fish finger sandwiches, a rockpool salad, and red currant & strawberry iced sea lollies.

episodes.name: The Karaoke Party
episodes.overview: Matilda is throwing a pop music party! She & her siblings head to a famous recording studio to make a special song for the party. In the kitchen Matilda's composing a menu of poptastic food!

episodes.name: The LA Make-Over
episodes.overview: Soaking up the best of Californian street style, Matilda's sisters Holly, Megan & family friend Elspeth hit the shops to get the perfect L.A look. Food here is super fashionable, so Matilda is inspired to cook some L.A favs.

episodes.name: The Fitness Training
episodes.overview: Matilda & the Ramsay Bunch hit the beach for a healthy dose of competitive fun with sports mad dad, Gordon, who has arranged a circuit of fitness training right on the famous Santa Monica beach front.

episodes.name: The Mexican Party
episodes.overview: Matilda & the Ramsay Bunch plan a Mexican party - with a twist. Dad Gordon is always teasing his kids so they're planning their revenge by building a customised pinata which looks just like their famous father!

episodes.name: The Daredevils
episodes.overview: Matilda & the Ramsay Bunch are flying high in more ways than one. Dad Gordon & mum Tana are taking the family on their first ever helicopter ride. The family is visiting Catalina Island for a hair-raising adventure.

episodes.name: The Big Good Bye
episodes.overview: Matilda & the Ramsay Bunch say goodbye to sunny California before flying home. Together, they'll look back on all of their favourite moments, from a beach BBQ feast & surf lesson to zip lining, to whacking a Mexican pinata!

episodes.name: The Competition
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsays head straight to the beach, where they meet a surfing dog.

episodes.name: The Drive-In
episodes.overview: Matilda and her family organise a drive-in movie night in the back garden with their friend Cruz Beckham.

episodes.name: The Wild West
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay bunch set off on a road trip to the American Wild West.

episodes.name: The TV Show
episodes.overview: Matilda and her dad Gordon appear on James Corden's American TV programme.

episodes.name: The Sea Lion Rescue
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay bunch travel to the California Wildlife Center.

episodes.name: The Big Trip
episodes.overview: Matilda and her family travel to Las Vegas in Nevada where they get to train with Cirque du Soleil acrobats.

episodes.name: The Day Off
episodes.overview: The Ramsay family hits the Californian coast for a beach barbecue, and 13-year-old Matilda takes the day off, handing over the job of cooking lunch to her sisters Megan and Holly. As the girls get cooking, brother Jack is given a lesson on how to fly a drone and use it to film incredible shots. Matilda's dad Gordon and Jack later go fishing on a jet ski, hoping for a big catch.

episodes.name: The Number One Sport
episodes.overview: The Ramsay family gets into American football, with Jack, Megan and Holly going training with a professional team called the Inglewood Blackhawks. later, they enjoy some cheerleader training with the athletic LA Dream All Stars, and learn how Americans support their teams. Meanwhile, Matilda makes a dinner to celebrate the sport, kicking off with Sloppy Joes and Touch Down Dip and Chips, followed by cherry pie.

episodes.name: The Concert
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay Bunch find out what it takes to become a rock star.

episodes.name: The Ramsay Pirates
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay bunch travel to the Cornish seaside and set sail on a raft.

episodes.name: The Beach Race
episodes.overview: Matilda Ramsay and her family travel to Watergate Bay beach on the Cornish coast.

episodes.name: The Birthday
episodes.overview: It's mum Tana's birthday, so the gang are planning to make it really special.

episodes.name: The Massive Jump
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay Bunch go coasteering on the rocky Cornish coastline.

episodes.name: The Last Days of Summer
episodes.overview: Matilda and her family are back home in London to throw a party for their friends.

episodes.name: The Holiday Finale
episodes.overview: Matilda Ramsay and her family make food and have fun. Matilda and the Ramsay bunch climb up, over and down one of the tallest buildings in London.

episodes.name: The Ramsays are Go
episodes.overview: As the summer gets under way Tilly, dad Gordon, mum Tana and sisters Megan and Holly get ready for their holiday, but first they need to pack off brother Jack as he leaves on a water polo tour with his team. They also need to say goodbye to their dogs Rumpole and Bruno, as they head to the kennels for their own holiday. A good send-off would never be complete without some delicious food so Tilly whips up some supertasty treats, including a giant lip-smacking burger, a scrummy peanut butter milk shake and some delicious power balls, packed with vitamins. For the dogs, there are some special doggy biscuits on the menu. But before they can tuck in to the food, there's some pampering to be done, including doggy bath time and a full-on Ramsay girls makeover for Jack!

episodes.name: The B Ball Match
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay bunch hit the Venice Beach basketball courts to shoot hoops with some of the coolest basketball players in Los Angeles. Sisters Megan and Holly head to the court with their friends to get some one on one coaching whilst Tilly does what she loves best - cooking up some delicious basketball-inspired food. To keep energy up on the court she's rustling up amazing slam-dunk meatball subs, terribly tasty basketball pizza pies and to cool everyone down in the hot Californian sun, fro-yo super ice lollies. Tilly arrives with her courtside picnic and after tucking in and demolishing the food, the guys split into teams and have a three-on-three basketball competition.

episodes.name: The Big Zen
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay Bunch try to answer an important family question: Is it better to have a relaxing day or an action-packed adventure? Tilly and sisters Megan and Holly are planning a special Ramsay girls' day out for mum Tana. But is it going to be a chilled-out zen-fest or an action-packed fun fiesta? Tilly is getting to work on a super-healthy beach picnic for her green goddess mum - crunchy rainbow veg with a scrummy spiced bean dip, lean mean chicken and airy raspberry macarons. Or should that be macaroons? Before dad Gordon turns up to help cook a beach barbecue, the four Ramsay girls try out the latest LA fad, yoga paddleboarding. Fingers crossed it will be the break from the chaos that mum deserves - ommmmm!

episodes.name: Return of The Jack
episodes.overview: Tilly’s big brother Jack has been away on tour with his water polo team, but now he is back and Tilly is cooking his favourite food for a slap-up, welcome-home lunch. Unfortunately she has got to put up with interfering dad Gordon as he tries to muscle into the kitchen to help her cook her meaty loaded lasagne and green courgette fries. Jack is sport and food mad, so this tasty and healthy lunch should be perfect before they hit the pool for a water polo competition with a twist… it is played in canoes! As all the Ramsay Bunch struggle to stay upright in their super-wobbly canoes, will it be tippy Team Tilly or generally wobbly Team Jack that win the match?

episodes.name: The Toughest Challenge Ever
episodes.overview: The Ramsay bunch are having a fab summer in Los Angeles but it's getting serious as Matilda and her brother Jack go head to head, racing against each other in one of LA's toughest sporting events - the gruelling pier-to-pier swimming race. They have to swim two and a half miles against a strong current, in the cold and very rough Pacific Ocean. Even though sporty dad Gordon has been coaching Tilly, Jack is still convinced he can beat her. Because she is otherwise engaged, Tilly has been very organised and left video instructions for mum Tana to make a delicious post-race re-booster - a fruity smoothie bowl. But before they get to eat that, it is a nerve-wracking time for the Ramsay bunch as they wait to see if Jack and Tilly can complete the toughest challenge they have ever taken on and make it safely back to dry land. To cap off an incredible day, Tilly cooks a celebratory brunch of champions - delicious American waffles with letter eggs and oven-baked chicken.

episodes.name: The LA Dogs
episodes.overview: Megan, Holly and their friends meet a Californian canine celebrity, while Tilly tracks down the other dogs people in LA love - hot dogs.

episodes.name: The Grand Prix
episodes.overview: Tilly and the Ramsays hold the first ever Ramsay Wacky Races and head to the go-kart track to see who the fastest driver is.

episodes.name: The Wedding Anniversary
episodes.overview: To celebrate dad Gordon and mum Tana's 20th wedding anniversary, Tilly prepares a Mexican feast and the biggest cake she's ever made.

episodes.name: The Lip Sync Challenge
episodes.overview: Megan and Holly head off to the dance studio to learn some Californian dance moves, while Tilly gets to work in the kitchen composing a pop-inspired lunch.

episodes.name: The Fishing Trip
episodes.overview: Gordon has organised a secret trip into the Californian countryside for Tilly, mum Tana and sister Holly, but the last thing they are expecting is fishing.

episodes.name: The Ramsay Games
episodes.overview: Tilly and the gang are preparing for the biggest, the best and the most important sporting event of the entire summer - the Ramsay Games.

episodes.name: The BBQ Beef
episodes.overview: Tilly takes part in the famous Long Beach barbecue competition. She sends Megan and Holly off to spy on the competitors while she gets to work.

episodes.name: The Ramsay Vloggers
episodes.overview: Inspired by a glamorous red carpet event they attended, Tilly, Megan, Holly, Jack set out to document stories about Hollywood.

episodes.name: The Old Man's Birthday
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay bunch are back in Britain and Tilly gets ready to cook a very special meal for dad Gordon's 50th birthday.

episodes.name: The Ramsays Connected
episodes.overview: Tilly puts together her digital summer scrapbook so she can look back at the best bits from the family's adventures in California.

episodes.name: The Sunday Lunch
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay bunch cook Britain's favourite meal - a classic Sunday roast with all the trimmings.

episodes.name: The Survivalists
episodes.overview: Dad Gordon puts the Ramsay bunch through their paces to see if they've got what it takes to survive in the wilderness.

episodes.name: The White Water Rush
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay bunch take on white-water rapids with one of Britain's most successful Olympians, kayak gold medallist Joe Clarke.

episodes.name: The Marathon Girl
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay Bunch are on tenterhooks as Tilly's big sister Megan takes part in the London Marathon.

episodes.name: The Big Bike Bite
episodes.overview: Tilly and Jack take over the show and go bike crazy. They head to one of the coolest BMX parks in the country and meet up with champion BMX rider Matti Hemmings.

episodes.name: The Snake Boy
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay Bunch cook for the animals at London Zoo - the human kind! Jack and Megan head straight to the reptile house!

episodes.name: La Festa Italiana: Part One
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay bunch take off for a sky-high adventure as Tilly attempts an incredible cooking first, making a meal at 30,000 feet.

episodes.name: La Festa Italiana: Part Two
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay bunch are on the Italian island of Sardinia where Tilly cooks her take on a classic Italian fish stew.

episodes.name: The Make-over
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay bunch undertake a major fashion challenge - to give Jack the ultimate makeover and turn him into the coolest boy at his party.

episodes.name: The Dragon Racers
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay bunch take part in one of the summer's most exciting competitions - the London dragon boat race.

episodes.name: The Hospital Challenge
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay bunch are on a mission to relieve the boredom of the patients in Great Ormond Street Hospital.

episodes.name: The Ballerinos
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay bunch train with the English National Ballet. Tilly sends her rugby-mad brother and his teammates off to improve their game.

episodes.name: The Perfect Day
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay bunch are on holiday in Cornwall and Tilly is determined to give everyone the perfect day.

episodes.name: The Lifeboat Rescue
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Ramsay bunch join the Padstow lifeboat team and Tilly and Gordon get to take part in a rescue mission.

episodes.name: The Ramsays Return
episodes.overview: After an amazing summer Matilda and the Ramsay bunch pack themselves into the car for the journey home, and it proves to be as eventful as the holiday itself.

episodes.name: High Stakes
episodes.overview: Tilly is taking on her dad Gordon in a barbecue face-off. Tilly also invites one of California’s hottest DJs, DJ Slushii, to come over and give her bother Jack a lesson.

episodes.name: The Scariest Ride
episodes.overview: The Bunch hold a competition to find out which Ramsay has the steeliest nerves. Tilly makes a chill-out potion full of calming ingredients.

episodes.name: The Coolest Sport in LA
episodes.overview: It’s very hot in California, but Matilda and her family are staying cool as they go ice hockey training. Tilly serves leak and potato soup and chicken sliders.

episodes.name: The Fresh Eggs of Bel Air
episodes.overview: Tilly expands the Ramsay family and gets fresh eggs to cook with by setting up a chicken farm in their Bel Air back garden.

episodes.name: The Ramsay Prankers
episodes.overview: Matilda and the Bunch plan to pull off the biggest and best Father's Day dad prank ever. To make sure it's spectacular they call one of the greatest pranksters they know.

episodes.name: The Disappearing Dad
episodes.overview: There's magic in the air when Tilly wishes she had to power to make her annoying dad Gordon simply disappear!

episodes.name: The Total Wipe-outs
episodes.overview: Tilly and the Bunch are learning how to do some cool new Californian adventure sports and wiping out big time as they do it.

episodes.name: The Hollywood Actor
episodes.overview: Tilly helps her brother Jack pursue his ambition to become an actor and asks Victoria Baldeserra from The Next Step to give him a few tips.

episodes.name: The Game
episodes.overview: The Bunch are making their very own computer game in one of the best motion capture studios in Los Angeles.

episodes.name: The Crazy Californians
episodes.overview: When Tilly answers the front door she gets the biggest surprise of the summer: two Nigerian dwarf goats have turned up to give the whole family a taste of goat yoga.

episodes.name: The Fastest Food
episodes.overview: Tilly is on a mission to surprise her parents with the craziest fast food takeaway meal they have ever had, roping in all the Bunch to help.

episodes.name: The Cornish Cake-off
episodes.overview: The baking battle lines are drawn in the kitchen for the first Ramsay Cornish Cake-off. Tilly is determined to win and become the queen of cakes.

episodes.name: The Big Dad Challenge
episodes.overview: Gordon sets down a summer challenge to his son Jack: can he complete a gruelling 1.1-mile open water swim across the Cornish Camel estuary in under 40 minutes?

episodes.name: The Banging Race
episodes.overview: The Ramsays put their feet to the floor for a high-speed Cornish adventure as dad Gordon gives Tilly her first driving lesson - in a banger racing car!

episodes.name: The Last Day of Summer
episodes.overview: Tilly rounds up her brother and sisters and they set sail on a fishing trip around the beautiful Cornish coast.
